{"履修期": "春学期後半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course focuses on Japan's financial system, with particular reference to corporate finance. In this course, students will learn about Japan's financial system, financial institutions, and financial markets, including financial intermediation. The course will review the functions of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Bank of Japan, the Financial Services Agency, and the banking system to efficiently deploy funds to entrepreneurs. Finally, the course will shed light on the determination of interest rates, the time value of money, and Japan's foreign exchange transactions.", "到達目標": "After completing the course, students will learn the features of the Japanese financial system, financial institutions, financial markets, and financial instruments in providing&nbsp; finance to corporations. Besides, students learn the basics of interest rates, the time value of money, and crowdfunding. The course is beneficial for advanced electives in corporate finance and financial management.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">economics, management, basic finance</span></span></span></span>", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "This is a face-to-face format class.&nbsp; Course pedagogy includes lectures, articles, and case studies to illustrate and reinforce concepts. Students are expected to have read the assigned materials\n  before attending each class. The instructor will supply all the reading materials in advance.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">【Startup Week】Online class (On-demand class) /《90minutes》</span></span></span></span><div><span style=\"font-siz